Subject: Make the Windows ZIP-fallback update accept the release channel

`_update_via_zip` is the `nadia update` fallback on Windows when git file I/O is
broken (antivirus/NTFS filter drivers) or there is no .git directory. It guards
`if branch != "main": sys.exit(1)` — upstream's way of refusing to silently
update from a non-default channel. After patch 0009 the resolved default branch
is "release", so the DEFAULT `nadia update` on this path now always trips the
guard and aborts: Windows customers (exactly the population this fallback exists
to rescue) can never complete an update. Flip the guarded/advised channel from
"main" to "release" so the default is accepted; the ZIP URL then resolves to
`archive/refs/heads/release.zip` (the runnable rebranded tree), and the
extracted-dir scan already tolerates the `nadia-release/` folder name. Passing a
non-release `--branch` is still (correctly) refused.

Mirrors 0006 (install.sh BRANCH), 0009 (cmd_update branch), 0011 (install.ps1
$Branch). IU-FR-7, IU-AC-9.

--- a/hermes_cli/main.py
+++ b/hermes_cli/main.py
@@ -6983,7 +6983,7 @@ def _update_via_zip(args):
     # bug --branch was added to prevent. Refuse to proceed in that case
     # rather than lie.
     branch = _resolve_update_branch(args)
-    if branch != "main":
+    if branch != "release":
         print(
             f"✗ --branch={branch} is not supported on the Windows ZIP-fallback "
             "update path."
@@ -6992,7 +6992,7 @@ def _update_via_zip(args):
             "  This path runs when git file I/O is broken on the system. "
             "Either resolve the git-side breakage (typically an antivirus "
             "or NTFS filter holding files open) and rerun `hermes update "
-            f"--branch {branch}`, or update against main with `hermes update`."
+            f"--branch {branch}`, or update against release with `hermes update`."
         )
         sys.exit(1)
     zip_url = (
